    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - 2000, 4000, 8000 - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="5">
            <title>HOOD</title>
            <para>The fiberglass hoods are one-piece type (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900201">Figure 1</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900202">Figure 2</hotlnk>). The narrowed tilt fiberglass hoods (except for original
                2000 series hood) provide aerodynamics, while still enclosing the air cleaner.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900201" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900201.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. 2000 Series Hoods</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0900202" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900202.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. 4000 and 8000 Series Hoods</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The original hood for the 2500 and 2600 models have an optional tilt hood with service access hatches
                on each side of the hood (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900203">Figure 3</hotlnk>). The access hatches allow routine checking of engine oil
                and coolant levels, it also allows changing the air cleaner element, without tilting the entire hood.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900203" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900203.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. 2500 and 2600 Optional Hood with Access Hatches</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 2000 HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SERVICE ACCESS HATCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The 2600 model has a new aerodynamic style hood, after March 1996 (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900204">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900204" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900204.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. 2600 Aerodynamic Hood (After March 1996)</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The hood for the 4000 series has an optional tilt hood with a service access hatch across the front of
                the hood (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900205">Figure 5</hotlnk>). The access hatch allows routine checking of engine oil and
                coolant levels without tilting the entire hood.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900205" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900205.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. 4000 Optional Hood with Access Hatch</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 4000 HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SERVICE ACCESS HATCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
